## Props (conceptual → `Button.tsx`)

Map design intent to code as follows (extend `Button` when a variant is missing):

| Design sheet | Suggested `variant` / notes |
|----------------|----------------------------|
| Primary solid navy | `primary` (today) |
| Primary subdued sky | add `primarySubdued` **or** `variant="primary"` + `tone="subdued"` when implemented |
| Ghost outline | overlap with `secondary` on light BG; use explicit ghost classes when on dark BG |
| Secondary filled light | add `secondarySolid` **or** extend `secondary` with `appearance="outline" \| "filled"` |
| Tertiary pale | `tertiary` (today) |
| Disabled | `disabled` |
| Loading | `loading` |

**Current implementation note:** `src/app/components/Button.tsx` exposes `variant`: `primary` | `secondary` | `tertiary` and sizes including icon-only. **New** sheet rows (primary subdued, filled secondary) should be added here first, then implemented in `Button.tsx` — do not fork one-off colours in pages.

---

## Special cases (outside matrix)

- **Save & Publish:** `bg-[#21c179] text-white hover:bg-[#1aa866]` (success).
- **Legacy CTA:** Some pages use `rounded-lg` / older hover `#003377` — migrate to this doc when touching those files.

---

## Do / don’t

- **Do** pick variant + size + content layout from the matrix before inventing new styles.
- **Do** keep disabled and loading visually subordinate (no competing saturation with enabled primary).
- **Don’t** embed `#004299` / `#00b8f5` inside SVG paths — use `currentColor` on icons inside buttons.
- **Don’t** use Tailwind ambiguous text scales for button labels — use the px sizes in the table.
